# Dish Builder Project Guidelines

This is a React + PHP recipe generator app hosted on Hostinger.

## General behavior

- Make minimal, focused changes.
- Do not refactor unrelated logic.
- Preserve the existing visual style unless the task explicitly asks for a redesign.
- Keep the soft green/cream Dish Builder styling consistent.
- Keep desktop and mobile layouts responsive.
- After changes, summarize modified files and what changed.

## Frontend

- Use existing React structure and components where possible.
- Reuse existing UI patterns instead of creating duplicate systems.
- Keep buttons, cards, rounded corners, shadows, and spacing consistent with the current design.
- For mobile fixes, preserve desktop styling unless explicitly asked otherwise.

## i18n

- The app uses react-i18next.
- Do not create a second i18n setup.
- Keep English as default language.
- Keep Russian as the second language.
- Update both locales/en.json and locales/ru.json when adding visible UI text.
- Do not use country flags.
- Keep the language switcher text-only: EN / RU.
- Static UI text should use translation keys.
- User-generated recipe content should not be translated through i18n.
- Generated recipes should follow the selected language through the recipe generation request.

## Backend and security

- PHP backend files live under api/.
- Do not expose database credentials, OpenAI API keys, or Pexels API keys to the frontend.
- Keep secrets server-side only.
- Use prepared SQL statements.
- Authenticated user data must be scoped to the current user only.
- API responses should be valid JSON.
- Do not output PHP warnings/notices into JSON responses.

## API usage

- Avoid unnecessary OpenAI API calls while debugging.
- Avoid unnecessary Pexels API calls while debugging.
- When testing API-related features, use the smallest number of real API calls possible.
- Prefer inspecting code, logs, and environment configuration before making repeated live API requests.

## Saved recipes

- Saved recipes should display with structured sections where possible.
- Reuse existing recipe display components if possible.
- Keep support for older saved recipes that may be stored as plain text.
- Saved recipe deletion must require authentication and must only affect the current user’s recipes.

## Weekly meal planner

- Preserve the existing planner behavior unless the task explicitly asks to change functionality.
- Keep meal planner cards visually consistent with the rest of the app.
- Keep mobile layout as one card per row.
- Keep desktop layout responsive and readable.